rComments: I thought Mrs. Costain did a good job helping understand something I couldn't care less about, poetry. The class was not easy but not overly difficult. Only distraction I ever had was her but that's my fault really.
Mrs. Costain was an alright English teacher. She is a tough marker but in first year classes that's expected. In her defence she's teaching poetry and her interest is medieval literature.

Worst prof I've had in uni. She was rude and made impossibly hard tests that did not at all test on the skills we were supposed to be developing (poetry analysis), but rather tested on your memorization skills. Encouraged participation, yet shut people down if their interpretation was "wrong." Very dull lecturer. Avoid if possible.
